 In a manner similar to a document, when you open any file within Animal
 Shelter Manager, what you get is a personal copy of it on the screen -
 it is not submitted to the database for other people to view until you
 explicitly save your changes, and when you do, everything is sent.
 If you make changes to an animal record and forget to save it, the system
 will pick up on this and ask you if you want to save, to make sure you
 do not lose your changes.
\end_layout

