reservation
\end_layout

\end_inset

 of animals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To start with, it is best to explain how the movement system works; each
 movement record represents a leaving and returning transaction.
 You can therefore only have one (or no) active movement record at a time.
 ie.
 No more than one unreturned movement.
 This is because the animal cannot leave the shelter in two different ways
 without being returned first.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A special exception to this is reservations - since they are not actually
 a movement (the animal hasn't gone anywhere), you can have one or more
 reservations as well as an open movement.
 You should turn the reservation into an adoption movement when the animal
 is adopted and cancel any other outstanding reservations (if it detects
 multiple reservations, ASM will prompt and cancel other reservations for
 you when you turn one into an adoption).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any method by which an animal leaves your shelter requires a movement record
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
movement record
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The only exception is death, which is handled through the animal death
 tab.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some common situations are listed below, along with what you should do:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
A new owner reserves the animal
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
Create a new movement record and fill out the reservation information.
 If there is a previous record with a reservation on and no movement, then
 fill in its reservation cancelled date (unless your shelter allows different
 people to reserve the same animal, in which case the system is happy to
 do this).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
An owner phones up and cancels their reservation
\series default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Find the movement record and fill out the reservation cancelled date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
An owner adopts the animal after reservation
\series default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Find the reservation record and fill out the adoption movement information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
A volunteer fosters the animal
\series default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Create a new movement record and fill out a foster movement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
An animal is returned from fostering
\series default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Find the fostering movement and fill in the return date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
An animal is returned from adoption
\series default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Find the adoption movement and fill in the return date.
\end_layout

