\begin_layout Subsection
The Match Point System
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Match Point System
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ASM uses a match point algorithm to determine how close the match is between
 the lost and found animal (or similar shelter animal, which it will also
 check for).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where the system compares two user defined pieces of text (eg.
 Distinguishing features), the system will represent the final score as
 the number of words from the lost animal field that appeared in the found
 animal field, expressed as a fraction of the total points available for
 that field.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, suppose I had a lost animal with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

white paws, bell
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for the distinguishing features.
 If there was a found animal with features 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

white paws, torn ear and a bell
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, that would constitute a 100% match on that particular field because every
 single word from the lost animal field appeared in the found animal field.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If I had a found animal with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

white paws, no collar
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for the distinguishing features, that would constitute a 66% match, because
 the match was 2/3 words.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By default, the system scores lost/found matches in this manner (all of
 these point values and how many points are required to appear can be changed
 in 
\series bold
System->Options
\series default
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:System-Options"

\end_inset

):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Same Species
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Same colour
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Same age group
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Same breed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - proportional match based on words of Area Lost/Found (ie 5 points
 maximum for 100% match of all words in Area Lost being present in Area
 Found)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Postcode match
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - proportional match based on words of Distinguishing Features
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Same Colour
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
5 points - Found within 2 weeks of being lost
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It therefore follows that 45 points is a 100% overall match.
 
\end_layout

