\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
ASK
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ask is quite a detailed key, which requests information from the user at
 generation time.
 The basic syntax is this:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
$ASK [DATE | [ALL]ANIMAL | LITTER | SPECIES | LOCATION | TYPE | NUMBER |
 STRING] [Message]$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that if you are substituting any kind of string value (ASK DATE or
 ASK STRING), you must wrap the ASK key inside string delimiters (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

 or ') otherwise you will get SQL errors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The types are outlined below:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK DATE message$
\series default
 - requests a date from the user.
 A popup is displayed containing the message and the user is given an ASM
 date control to use to select the date.
 The value substituted is the date selected by the user in SQL string format
 appropriate for the database you are using.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK ANIMAL$ 
\series default
- requests an animal.
 A popup displays a list of all animals on the shelter.
 The value substituted is the animal ID.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK ALLANIMAL$ 
\series default
- requests an animal.
 A popup displays a list of all animals in the database.
 The value substituted is the animal ID.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK LITTER$
\series default
 - requests a litter identifier.
 A popup displays a list of the recent, active litters on the system.
 The value returned is the litter ID as a string.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK SPECIES$
\series default
 - requests a species from the user.
 A popup is displayed containing a dropdown of all species on the system
 with an additional entry for 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 The value substituted is the ID of the selected species, or 0 if 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 was selected (use the SQL CASE statement to adapt the WHERE clause for
 all)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK LOCATION$
\series default
 - requests an internal location from the user in the same manner as $ASK
 SPECIES$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK VOUCHER$
\series default
 - requests a voucher from the user in the same manner as $ASK SPECIES$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK DIET$
\series default
 - requests a diet from the user in the same manner as $ASK SPECIES$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK TYPE$
\series default
 - requests an animal type from the user in the same manner as $ASK SPECIES$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK NUMBER message$
\series default
 - requests a numeric value from the user.
 A box is popped up containing the message and the user is given a standard
 text box to enter the number in.
 They will not be allowed to continue until a valid number is entered.
 The value returned is the number.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
$ASK STRING message$
\series default
 - requests a string value from the user (eg: Name, Address, etc.).
 A box is popped up containing the message and the user is given a text
 box to enter the string in.
 The value substituted is the string.
\end_layout

