\begin_layout Standard
Often, it is difficult to get all the information you need to generate a
 report together in one single query.
 ASM's custom report editor allows you to enter multiple SQL instructions,
 separated by a semi-colon (;)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This works just like any SQL console editor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can use this feature to create temporary tables of information and populate
 them with multiple queries.
 The only stipulation ASM makes is that the last query in your set MUST
 be a SELECT query (returning the results of the temporary table).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ASM will automatically detect your usage of CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE and clean
 them up for you, so you do not need to add 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

DROP TABLE x
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 queries.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Eg: This simple query set will aggregate all the animal names into a separate
 table which can then be output by a custom report:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE tt$USER$ ( aname varchar(50) );
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
INSERT INTO tt$USER$ (aname) SELECT AnimalName FROM animal;
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
SELECT * FROM tt$USER$
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note the use of the $USER$ SQL tag to make sure the temporary table is unique
 for each user.
 The ASM custom report editor is capable of syntax checking all queries
 and autogenerating the correct HTML from a multi-query set.
\end_layout

