\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Each row in your result data becomes a point on the X axis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The first column in each row is assumed to contain the name used for the
 label on the X axis.
 Only string data should be used for the first column.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Each subsequent column is assumed to be a piece of data at that point on
 the X axis (and thus gives the Y axis its scale).
 Only numeric data can appear in columns after the first one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The fieldname of each column after the label column is used to denote the
 data on the legend.
\end_layout

