 and the moment the last one has left the shelter through a means other
 than fostering (if the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Foster animals are shelter inventory
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 option is on), the litter will be cancelled.
 This method is 100% accurate and once you have entered the litter, you
 do not have to do anything else - the system will take care of it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the litter logger main screen, you can highlight a litter and call
 up all the animals in that litter.
 The litter logger main screen will also show you how many of the litter
 animals are currently left on the shelter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This method works best when employed with the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

after a specific time period
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

