\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ASM allows you to choose the format that animal codes will be automatically
 generated in.
 ASM internally stores two codes for each animal, the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

normal
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 code, unique among all animals and the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

short
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 code.
 The short code does not have to be unique and is used by staff wanting
 to quickly identify animals in conversation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The defaults are TYYYYNNN (the first letter of the animal type, followed
 by the year it was brought to the shelter, followed by a number unique
 within that year for that type of animal) for the normal code and NNT for
 the shortcode (a unique number within the year for the animal's type, followed
 by the type).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can build and use any format string you like, using the following tokens:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
YYYY - The year the animal was brought into the shelter (4 digits)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
YY - The year the animal was brought into the shelter (2 digits)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
MM - The month the animal was brought into the shelter
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DD - The day the animal was brought into the shelter
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
T - The first letter of the animal's type
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
UUUUUUUUUU - (10 digits) a unique number representing the animal (this number
 will never be used for another animal), padded to 10 digits.
 If the number overflows, more digits will be used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
UUUU - (4 digits) a unique number representing the animal (this number will
 never be used for another animal), padded to 4 digits.
 If the number overflows, more digits will be used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
NNN - (3 digits) a number representing the animal, which is unique within
 the year brought in for the animal's type and padded to 3 digits.
 If the number overflows, more digits will be used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
NN - A number representing the animal, which is unique within the year brought
 in for the animal's type.
 No padding is done.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here are some examples:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
YYYYMMDD-NNN-T (an ISO date, followed by a unique number/type within the
